A new species of the spider genus Naevius Roth from Argentina (Araneae, Amaurobiidae, Macrobuninae)Naevius calilegua spec. nov. is described from yungas in Jujuy Province, Argentina. Naevius species bear a conspicuous tibial gland, discharging through a movable dorsal tibial apophysis. This character relates Naevius to the macrobunine genera Emmenomma and Anisacate.